@bangolufsen is expanding its Recreated Classics programme with a new, ultra-limited Beosystem 3000c “Dune Grey” edition, pairing restored Beogram 3000 turntables from the 1980s with modern Beolab 8 speakers. Hand-restored in Struer, Denmark, each vintage turntable is meticulously dismantled, repaired, and upgraded with dark-stained walnut detailing, bringing one of B&O’s most iconic designs into the modern era.⁠
⁠
Limited to 100 numbered units and priced at $30,000, the Beosystem 3000c reflects Bang & Olufsen’s commitment to longevity, craftsmanship, and circular design. Led by the company’s Recreated Classics initiative, the project aims to offer an alternative to short-lived consumer electronics by extending the lifespan of exceptional products while combining vintage design with contemporary streaming technology.⁠

